According to a media statement issued by Councillor TS Masilela, the employee was tested for the virus on 15 June after displaying symptoms. The test results came back positive on Wednesday and the municipal offices were closed with immediate effect. The Nkangala District Municipality will remain closed until 22 June as the facilities undergo cleaning and disinfecting. Tracing was done and all employees who have been in direct contact with the infected person will self-isolate for a 14 day period.